{"name":"System Guide","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Introduction","type":"text","_id":"SPv6z314GPBQuGBG","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Welcome to the <strong>Index Card RPG: Master Edition</strong> system for Foundry VTT!<br />This system is a fan-made project, released with Runehammer's permission and approval.</p><p>Have fun!</p><p></p><h2>Issues and feedback</h2><p>If you find any issues or bugs, you can report them <a href=\"https://github.com/ClipplerBlood/icrpgme/issues\">here</a>. If you want to provide some feedback or need some help, feel free to contact me on discord at ClipplerBlood#8146.</p><p></p><h2>Supporting the project</h2><p>If you like the project and want to support its development, you can buy me a coffee on Ko-fi! Many coffees were drank in the making of this project and with your help I'll be able to restock my cabinet :D</p><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/support.svg\" style=\"border:none;display:block;margin:0 auto\" /><p></p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Guide contents</span></h2><ol><li><p><strong>Characters: </strong>how to create &amp; use the character sheet.</p></li><li><p><strong>Monsters: </strong>creating and viewing monsters.</p></li><li><p><strong>Items: </strong>loot, abilities and how to automatically add bonuses to characters.</p></li><li><p><strong>Macros: </strong>how to quickly use your character in game.</p></li><li><p><strong>Obstacles: </strong>what they are and how to use.</p></li><li><p><strong>Combat Tracker: </strong>features &amp; how it works.</p></li><li><p><strong>ICRPG Tools: </strong>Targets, Timers and Index Cards</p></li><li><p><strong>System settings.</strong></p></li></ol><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Characters","type":"text","_id":"AOrGAwIfLJNghyI8","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Character Sheet overview</span></h2><p>The sheet uses the same design as the original ICRPG sheet, with a couple of adaptations for VTT play.</p><p>The character sheet has two modes: <strong>Locked</strong> and <strong>Unlocked</strong>.<br />To edit the attributes, items and other various stuff, you want to switch to unlock the sheet. To do so, click on top-right locked button and start editing!</p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Tabs</span></h2><ul><li><p><strong>Character Tab.</strong> All the character main stats and info are here.</p></li><li><p><strong>Loot &amp; Abilities</strong>. Here are Loot, Abilities, Powers and Augments</p></li><li><p><strong>Notes.</strong> A convenient place to store the your player's notes</p></li><li><p><strong>Resources: </strong>Here you can track resources like Mastery and SP, or anything else you may want to keep track of.</p></li></ul><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Character Tab</span></h2><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/character-sheet-1.webp\" /><ul><li><p><strong>A</strong>: <strong>Locked/Unlocked button</strong>. Use this to switch between view and edit mode.</p></li><li><p><strong>B:</strong> <strong>Character info.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>C: Attribute/Effort dice total</strong>. Click on this to make a roll!</p></li><li><p><strong>D:</strong> <strong>Attribute values</strong>. When the sheet is unlocked, you can put the values heres, which will be automatically added in the total (<strong>C</strong>)</p></li><li><p><strong>E:</strong> <strong>Number of hearts</strong>. When the sheet is unlocked, clicking on a heart will set the character number of hearts (max HP).</p></li><li><p><strong>F: Damage/Health total</strong>. Depending on the game setting (see the Game Settings page), it indicates the character's current damage or health.</p></li><li><p><strong>G:</strong> <strong>Defense, Hero Coin and Dying rounds</strong>. Note that you can modify the \"Defense Loot\" value inside the Defense shield. Also to make a Defense Attempt, you can click the shield.</p></li><li><p><strong>H:</strong> <strong>Tab navigation</strong>.</p></li></ul><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Loot &amp; Abilities Tab</span></h2><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/character-sheet-2.webp\" /><ul><li><p><strong>A: Max Equipped and Carried weight. </strong>When the sheet is unlocked you can edit here the maximum weights.</p></li><li><p><strong>B: Item name.</strong> When locked, clicking the name posts the item to chat. When unlocked, it edits the item name.</p></li><li><p><strong>C: Item description</strong>. Editable when unlocked.</p></li><li><p><strong>D: Equipped/Carried checkboxes.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>E: New Item name. </strong>It appears when the sheet is unlocked. To create a new item directly into the character, simply write the item name here and press enter. A new item will appear, and its description can be edited using (<strong>B</strong>)</p></li></ul><p><strong>Note: </strong>you can right click the items to open a context menu that allows you to <strong>Delete</strong> the item or <strong>Open </strong>its sheet for more advanced editing. See the Items guide section for more info.</p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Resources Tab</span></h2><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/character-sheet-3.webp\" /><ul><li><p><strong>A: Mastery</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>B: Resource name.</strong> When unlocked, here you can edit the tracked resource name</p></li><li><p><strong>C: Resource value and max.</strong> You can edit the tracked value (even when locked) and the maximum resource value (only when unlocked)</p></li><li><p><strong>D: New resource name. </strong>When unlocked, you can create a new resource to track by setting its name</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":300000,"name":"Monsters","type":"text","_id":"3hcaFdYA9sjvIhUp","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Like for the Character Sheet, the Monster Sheet also has the Locked/Unlocked mode.<br />The locked mode closely resembles the original ICRPG design for easier reference during game.<br />The unlocked mode has a different interface, used in creating and editing your monsters.</p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Monster sheet editing</span></h2><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/monster-sheet-1.webp\" /><ul><li><p><strong>A: Monster Name.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>B: Monster Hearts.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>C: Monster Attributes modifiers. </strong>The first option \"<strong>STATS</strong>\" represents the modifier for all <strong>ATTEMPTS</strong>. For example a monster with \"5 STATS\" makes each Attempt with a +5 modifier.</p></li><li><p><strong>D: Monster Efforts modifiers. </strong>The first option \"<strong>EFFORT</strong>\" represent the modifier for all effort rolls. Like for the above STATS modifier, a monster with \"5 EFFORT\" makes all effort rolls with a +5.</p></li><li><p><strong>E: Other mods. </strong>Here are a bunch of extras that monsters might have:</p><ul><li><p><strong>ALL ROLLS:</strong> A modifier for all rolls</p></li><li><p><strong>EXTRA ACTION:</strong> Here you can put some text that is added in the monster's stat block. For example \"2 ACTIONS/TURN\" or \"INDESTRUCTIBLE\".</p></li><li><p><strong>EXTRA HEALTH: </strong>Here goes text that will be placed in the same row as the hearts. For example, the Seraph's \"/ARM\" text or the Gerblin Traitors \"or 1 HP\" text.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>F: Monster Abilities. </strong>Here you can edit the ability's name and description.</p></li><li><p><strong>G: New Ability Name. </strong>To add a new ability, you can type its name in here and when pressing enter the ability is added.</p></li><li><p><strong>H: Description.</strong></p></li></ul><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">USING MONSTERS IN GAME</span></h2><p>To make a roll with a monster you can use the provided Macros. See the Macros section of this guide for more info.</p><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":412500,"name":"Obstacles","type":"text","_id":"pVvmLJ7FYxYgEhir","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">What is an obstacle?</span></h2><p>An obstacle is <strong>something that requires effort to complete</strong>, such as a task, a situation to resolve, an NPC to persuade or a generic obstacle.</p><p><br />Obstacles can be created using the same method used for creating a monster, or more quickly by using the button in the Combat Tracker.</p><p>The only features of an obstacle are its name, the number of hearts and an image. Note that obstacles cannot take actions.</p><p></p><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":500000,"name":"ICRPG Tools","type":"text","_id":"VQ1wDNUoS7XxT0Ez","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>From the sidebar on the left, you can access the ICRPG Tools.</p><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/controls.png\" style=\"display:block;margin:0 auto\" /><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Targets &amp; Timers</span></h2><p>By pressing the first and second button, you can create a new Target or Timer, respectively.</p><p>Once a timer or target is created, it will be shown for all players.</p><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/target-timer.png\" style=\"display:block;margin:0 auto\" /><p>The GM can edit their values and also close them.</p><p>In addition, targets can be set to \"easy\" and \"hard\" by pressing on the label.</p><p>Timers also have a name, useful for displaying more information to the players.</p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Index Cards</span></h2><p>The third button allows you to quickly sketch your ideas into Index Cards. When pressing the button, a window pops up and you can free-hand your sketch in here. Once you are done, press the \"Upload\" button and your sketch will be placed in the game canvas.</p><p>For more info and usage, refer to the module's guide <a href=\"https://foundryvtt.com/packages/sketch-tiles\">here</a></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":450000,"name":"Combat Tracker","type":"text","_id":"HDc6CWJgPG8UL0ig","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Combat tracker overview</span></h2><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/combat-1.webp\" style=\"margin:0 auto;display:block\" /><p>Since in ICRPG there isn't a monster initiative, but rather a player and GM ordering, the combat tracker works a bit differently from other Foundry systems.</p><p>For example, you can freely change the order of player characters as to simulate the \"round table\" turn order. In addition, the combat tracker is divided into three sections: Players, Gamemaster and Obstacles.</p><p>Tracker overview:</p><ul><li><p><strong>A: Initiative buttons. </strong>From left to right:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Roll initiative.</strong> All players roll a dice, and the highest player starts the round. Ties are resolved by their order in the tracker.</p></li><li><p><strong>Shuffle combatants.</strong> The order of the combatants is randomly shuffled.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>B: Health inputs.</strong> Here you can edit the combatant HP. Note that it depends on if tracking damage or tracking hp. To edit a combatant hp you can either:</p><ul><li><p>Manually adjust the hp. For example if the damage is 7 and the character takes 3 damage, change the input to 10</p></li><li><p>Adjust the relative hp, by adding the amound of damage (or subtracting it). In the previous example, if you input \"+3\" then the summation happens automatically, resulting in 10 damage total</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>C: Handles for ordering</strong>. You can change the order of combatants by dragging them with this handle</p></li><li><p><strong>D: Quick Obstacle creation. </strong>Pressing this button quickly creates an obstacle to track. For convenience, Obstacles created in this way are automatically placed in the \"Obstacles\" folder, inside the actors sidebar tab.</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":350000,"name":"Items","type":"text","_id":"Z3gKrtkWHiv89PRn","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The item sheet has two tabs:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Item</strong>: Where the description and images are displayed</p></li><li><p><strong>Bonuses</strong>: Where item bonuses and other stuff can be edited.</p></li></ul><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Automatic item bonuses</span></h2><p>There are two ways of handling the items in this system:</p><ul><li><p>Traditional <em>\"Form Filling\" </em>where the player manually edits their character sheet with the relevant bonuses from items, just like in a paper sheet</p></li><li><p>Automated way, where the GM fills in the bonuses for each item and the player simply drags and drops the items into their character sheet, and all the bonuses get automatically added to the sheet. Loots must be equipped for their bonuses to apply, while other items' bonuses are always added.</p></li></ul><p>There is no right or wrong way of doing items, so feel free to use what you prefer!</p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Item Sheet editing</span></h2><img src=\"systems/icrpgme/assets/system-guide/item-sheet-1.webp\" /><ul><li><p><strong>A: Attributes and Effort bonuses. </strong>Here go the Attempt and Effort bonuses (or maluses)</p></li><li><p><strong>B: Weight. </strong>Here you can set the item's weight (loots only) or bonuses to the carried or equipped capacity. For example the \"Traveler's Garb\" extra spaces would go here.</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":375000,"name":"Macros","type":"text","_id":"wqJHCyBbNEcMzeEP","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Included Macros</span></h2><p>The system comes with three macros categories:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Attempts</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Efforts</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Roll Selector</strong></p></li></ul><p></p><p>By default the macros are already set up in the hotbar, with the Roll Selector and Attempts in the first macro row, and Efforts in the second row.</p><p></p><p>They all work similarly, by performing a roll on the <em>currently selected token.</em> <br />For example, if you wish to roll a Strength Attempt on a character, you have to select the relative token and then use the macro with \"Attempt Strength\". The same goes for Effort macros.</p><p></p><p>The <strong>Roll Selector</strong> macro is a bit different. Instead of doing a roll, the macro opens a small dialog with all the character attributes &amp; efforts. Then you can conveniently select whatever roll you like and the dialog won't close automatically.</p><p>Once the dialog is open, when switching tokens the valued used for rolls automatically update, so it's perfect for controlling different monster types in a single encounter.</p><p></p><h2><span style=\"font-family:Nusaliver\">Advanced macros</span></h2><p>Roll macros use the following code:</p><pre><code>game.icrpgme.macros.rollSelected('&lt;attributes/efforts&gt;', '&lt;attribute/effort name&gt;', &lt;modifier&gt;)</code></pre><p>By editing this macro you can make quick rolls for items that add a modifier to one of you rolls only when using them. For example the \"Weapon Gem\" that gives a +2 effort bonus could be done with</p><pre><code>game.icrpgme.macros.rollSelected('efforts', 'weapons', 2)</code></pre>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":600000,"name":"Settings","type":"text","_id":"ZpY9oCEXRkoCh7Ww","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Available settings</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Track Damage: </strong>when ON, the character sheets and combat tracker use \"damage\"(additive) instead of \"HP\" (subtractive). This means that instead of subtracting the damage received to the current HP, you add the damage.<br /></p></li><li><p><strong>Show monsters HP to players:</strong> when ON, all players can see the monsters' hp. Note that:</p><ul><li><p>This applies only to monsters in the \"gamemaster\" section of the combat tracker. Monsters in the \"players\" section are treated as  allies/pets/evocations so players can see their health</p></li><li><p>Obstacles always display their HP</p></li></ul></li></ul><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.ObHPGJ3NvQ6ri7dX"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"icrpgme","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1665221864957,"modifiedTime":1665565427601,"lastModifiedBy":"RhjXh2pZgxD9uRAF"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"RhjXh2pZgxD9uRAF":3},"_id":"qmJoXVsdtPML7nrs"}
